				 Rabri fury over rickety govt car

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT
																								Patna, Dec. 7: Rabri Devi did a Lalu Prasad today while demonstrating her anger against the rickety official car sent to her on the opening day of the Assembly session. 
																								The Opposition leader made the official car follow the swanky, bullet-proof and private one that brought her to the House premises. Look at that (the official car). Its not bullet-proof, its windows are broken and the doors open by themselves, said a fuming Rabri Devi, while talking to reporters. She added: The Nitish Kumar government has allotted a rickety car to humiliate me. 
																								He (Nitish) talks of respecting democracy. Is it the way to treat the leader of the Opposition in a democracy? she asked. 
																								The minister who occupied 1, Anne Marg, has been complaining of logistics ever since Nitish Kumar replaced her as the chief minister.
																								She first complained of an ill-repaired and ill-maintained house after moving out of the 1, Anne Marg, residence. The house was more suitable for reptiles than human beings, she had said, right after she moved in. The government reacted instantly and got the house repaired and furnished. The question remains if the government would be as prompt in solving the leaders latest grievance. Lets see, said the state RJD chief, Abdul Bari Sidiqqui.

